Lagos - One of the more than 200 schoolgirls abducted by Islamist militant group Boko Haram from their school in northeast Nigeria&apos;s Chibok in 2014 has been found by soldiers, a Nigerian army spokesman said on Saturday.Sani Usman said the girl was discovered in Pulka, Gwoza Local Government Area, in Borno State, by troops who were screening escapees from Boko Haram&apos;s base in the Sambisa forest.The girl, Maryam Ali Maiyanga, was &#x201C;discovered to be carrying a 10-month-old son&#x201D;, the army spokesman said. Reuters